"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<h2>Crushing as physically breaking in pieces</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:21\">DEU 9:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:7\">2CH 34:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job39:14-Job39:15\">JOB 39:14–39:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa27:9\">ISA 27:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:40\">DAN 2:40</a></p>\n<h2>Crushing in the preparation of food and drink</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev2:14\">LEV 2:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev2:16\">LEV 2:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:8\">NUM 11:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:11\">JOB 24:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:15\">MIC 6:15</a></p>\n<h2>Crushing denoting physical violence</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:38-2Sam22:39\">2SA 22:38–22:39</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:5-Ps110:6\">PSA 110:5–110:6</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:5\">ISA 53:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:24\">LEV 22:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:1\">DEU 23:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job6:8-Job6:9\">JOB 6:8–6:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:15\">ISA 3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos2:13\">AMO 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:4\">MAL 1:4</a></p>\n<h2>Crushing used metaphorically</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:15\">GEN 3:15</a></strong> <em>Widely regarded as being the earliest prediction of Jesus Christ's triumph over Satan</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:14\">PRO 18:14</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:8\">2CO 4:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:2\">JOB 19:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:4\">PRO 15:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:44\">MAT 21:44</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:18\">LUK 20:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:20\">ROM 16:20</a></p>",
